# Solicitation Review: 70CMSW26I00000001

---

## Solicitation Overview
- **Title:** Boxed Meals at Broadview IL
- **Solicitation Number:** 70CMSW26I00000001
- **Agency:** U.S. Department of Homeland Security, U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) â€“ Mission Support Washington
- **Location:** ICE Detention Facility, Broadview, Illinois
- **Official Posting:** [sam.gov link](https://sam.gov/workspace/contract/opp/2c07aa2cdd6841e781b26767aac1fdcf/view)

---

## Scope & Requirements
- **Services:** Preparation, packaging, and delivery of 70 boxed meals per meal (breakfast, lunch, dinner) daily.
- **Nutritional Guidelines:** All meals must meet USDA Recommended Dietary Allowance (RDA) standards for calories, protein, fats, vitamins, and minerals.
- **Dietary Compatibility:** Programs must accommodate diets such as vegetarian, low-sodium, allergen-free (including gluten- and nut-free options).
- **Packaging:** Environmentally friendly, single-use, labeled with meal type and prep date.
- **Delivery:**
  - Breakfast by 6:00 AM
  - Lunch by 12:00 PM
  - Dinner by 6:00 PM
  - Must use temperature-controlled vehicles.

---

## Key Dates
- **Solicitation Released:** November 7, 2025
- **Response Due:** November 11, 2025 @ 12:00 PM EST

---

## Period of Performance
- **Initial Term:** Three (3) months from award date, with potential extension.

---

## Compliance, Security, and QA
- **Quality Assurance:** Contractor must maintain a QA plan. ICE reserves inspection rights.
- **Security:** Mandatory facility protocols, including background checks for delivery staff.
- **Menu Planning:** Weekly menus approved in advance; diet substitutions require prior government approval.

---

## Payment Terms
- **Monthly billing upon verified delivery and acceptance.** Invoice must detail meal numbers and compliance.

---

## Insurance Requirements
- **Insurance requirements are NOT specified in the available summary.**

---

## Contact & Submittals
- **Contact Information:** Not provided in summary; refer to sam.gov posting for official point of contact if needed.
- **Submissions:** Interested vendors to include a capability statement and relevant business data (company size, UEI, etc.).

---

## Included Documents
- Statement of Work (SOW) detailing requirements accompanies full solicitation materials.

---

## Salient Considerations
- **Highly prescriptive dietary, scheduling, and security requirements.**
- **Short turnaround time for responses (within ~4 days of posting).**
- **Site-specific performance (Broadview, IL).**
- **Insurance and direct contact info will need to be clarified if proceeding.**

---

### Recommendation
Careful evaluation is warranted, especially regarding insurance, facility security, and capacity to meet recurring, high-volume dietary requirements on a tight schedule. Full solicitation documents should be reviewed for omitted requirements (insurance, etc.) prior to immediate pursuit.
